Element tns:InternationalStringType / tns:LocalizedString
Namespace urn:oasis:names:tc:ebxml-regrep:xsd:rim:4.0
Diagram
Type tns:LocalizedStringType
Properties
content complex
minOccurs 0
maxOccurs unbounded
Attributes
QName Type Default Use Annotation
value tns:FreeFormText required
xml:lang union of(xs:language, restriction of xs:string) en-US optional
Attempting to install the relevant ISO 2- and 3-letter codes as the enumerated possible values is probably never going to be a realistic possibility. See RFC 3066 at http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc3066.txt and the IANA registry at http://www.iana.org/assignments/lang-tag-apps.htm for further information. The union allows for the 'un-declaration' of xml:lang with the empty string.

Complex Type tns:CommentType
Namespace urn:oasis:names:tc:ebxml-regrep:xsd:rim:4.0
Annotations
Models the familiar PostIt attached to papers metaphor. Used to attach comments to Register during registration procedures, may be used to comment on any RegistryObject. Implemented as a sub-type of ExtrinsicObjectType. If comment is small it is specified in description field. If comment is large or needs formatting, images etc. then it is specified in the RepositoryItem as a document. Adding a comment to a RegistryObject done by defining a HasComment Association with an ExtrinsicObject with objectType Comment.
